Like I said more than one way to do it.  
 
> I did lap welds because I can use a higher setting on my welder and get
> better penetration. When you butt weld thin metal, you have to cut the
> voltage way down and it takes more time to stitch such a long run. The
outer
> lap also leaves a small gutter that I use to make my transition to the
> existing panel using filler.

Personally I don't like to have to fill a "gutter" with filler.  Not that
it hurts anything...just a bit extra filler to have to work.

What ever works best for you.

